// desc:Multi Channel Spectrum Analyzer (Veto_gfxanalyzer)
// provides:
//   [windows] .
//   [darwin] .
// tags: analysis FFT meter spectrum multi channel
// author: Cockos/Veto
// version: 0.2.2
// screenshot:
//   https://i.imgur.com/faNmSdz.gif
// donation:
//   https://www.cockos.com/reaper/purchase.php
//   https://reapack.com/
// changelog:
//   # Tiny internal change (unambiguous effect description)
// about:
//   ## Description
//   Multi-channel mod of Cockos gfxanalyzer (Frequency Spectrum Analyzer Meter included in REAPER) by [Veto](https://forum.cockos.com/member.php?u=25032).
//   ![Image](https://i.imgur.com/USvPDCk.gif)
//   
//   See also [here](https://forum.cockos.com/showthread.php?t=200414).
//
//   ## Features
//   (additional to gfxanalyzer)
//    - Frequency/notes & amplitude readout
//    - Channel on/off switches
//    - Spectrum slope/tilt
//    - Opacity control
//    - Maximum contrast coloring
//    - customize plot colors by setting parameter values (see below)
//
//   ## Controls
//    - **left-click**: show/hide controls/readout
//
//   ## Customizing plot colors
//   By default colors of all stereo channels are hard-coded to have maximum human-perceivable contrast to each other and to the background.
//   Using for instance ReaScript the user can override this by setting values of effect parameters named `color 1-2`, `color 3-4` etc.
//   Values to be sent/received are RGB channels packed into 24bit int (`pc=r+g*256+b*65536`).
//
//   I include a script in my repo which modifies plot colors of the currently focused Veto_gfxanalyzer plugin to colors of tracks which send to stereo channels 1-16 on the receiving track
//   (fx-chain routing and plugin pin connection has to be unmodified).
//  
//   Look for a EEL script named `"Set colors of focused Veto_gfxanalyzer to tracks sending on channels 1-16.eel"`.
//  
//   **Short example (EEL):**
//  
//   This changes the color of stereo channel 15-16 to yellow.
//   The variable`fxID` needs to be set to the index of Veto_gfxanalyzer in the fx-chain of track `trkP`.
//   ```
//   function rpr_TrackFX_SetParamByName(track,fx,paramname,val) local(i,found,curNm) (
//     i=found=0;
//     while(i<TrackFX_GetNumParams(track,fx) && !found ) (
//       TrackFX_GetParamName(track,fx,i,curNm=#);
//       !strcmp(curNm,paramname) ? (
//         TrackFX_SetParam(track,fx,i,val);
//         found=1;
//       );
//       i+=1;
//     );
//     found;
//   );
//  
//   ...
//   rpr_TrackFX_SetParamByName(trkP,fxID,"color 15-16",255+255*256+0*65536);
//   ...
//   ```
//   Copyright (C) 2007 and later, [Cockos Incorporated](http://cockos.com/)
/*
Copyright (C) 2007 and later, Cockos Incorporated
